annotations: Left my soul in his vision

There is a semantic field of the “beyond”, such as clouds, the intangible “consciousness” and “soul”. suggesting that she feels detached from her body and earthly feelings. This emphasises how their love is not ordinary but instead exists on a deeper, spiritual level.

Wait a minute
 I think I left my conscience on your front doorstep, oh oh

When you’re really into someone, sometimes you leave everything behind and lose yourself in them. This is a really clever way of saying that.

Leaving your conscience for love can also be misunderstood. Your conscience determines what is right and wrong, so if it is left on their doorstep, it implies she no longer cares what is right and wrong while she is with them.

I’ll run my hands through your hair
 You wanna run your fingers through mine
 But my dreads too thick and that’s alright

Running your fingers through someone’s hair is a sign of affection, although since Willow has dreads, this task is a bit difficult.



In an interview, Willow expanded on her dreads, stating:

I just want to have dreads…I want to embrace my full self, as natural as I can be."
When you first said, “Oel ngati kameie”

Willow utilizes Na'vi, the language used in the popular film, Avatar. In Na'vi, this line means “I see you.”

Willow has used this language several times in her music, like in the track “Natives of the Windy Forest”:

Tsmukan sì tsmuke tireapängkxo"

She has also referenced it on her twitter:
https://twitter.com/OfficialWillow/status/598503639297236993

Wait a minute
 I think I left my consciousness in the sixth dimension

We currently imagine ourselves living in a 3-spacial-dimensional reality (4 if you count time), so a 6th dimension would mean being advanced and at a high state of mind/being/awareness.

As summarized by Ella Alderson, the sixth dimension is all of the possible futures, presents and pasts which could exist all starting with the big bang.

The chorus of the song eludes to a more lively and optimistic vibe that they both experience when they spend time together.

annotations: Man, this must be the life

If you’ve driven on the highway at night, then you know the feeling being described. It’s a transcendent experience, especially if accompanied by someone you love; both a warm fuzzy feeling of “everything will be okay” and a parallel appreciation of the beauty of a city (LA) at night.

This experience, importantly, is also very “teen/ young adult”. Driving in a car on the open road is often the first “taste of freedom” youth in the USA have. This feeds into the nostalgia vibe of the song.

While there is certainly more to life than driving on the highway at night, this moment shard by WILLOW and Tyler epitomizes (to them) what it means to be alive. We should note that this “epitomization” itself highlights the two’s youth, naivety, and innocence as this experience of driving at night is the “most adult” experience of freedom/ enjoyment of life they have. I.e., while they can’t own a home/ have a real job/ etc. they can enjoy the lights of the 405.
We can hit the 405
Interstate 405 or “The 405” is a large highway that runs through Los Angeles, from Lake Forest to San Fernando. It is the most heavily congested highway in the United States.

I’ll be so much stronger
 I’ll stay up for longer
This might be Willow recalling times in her childhood when she fantasized about being older and being able to do more things than a child.

I’m not getting younger
 But when I’m older

These two lyrics form a literary paradox. “Not getting younger” would seem to imply “getting older” and a degree of self awareness and maturity. In the next lyric, however, WILLOW talks about “getting older” with a childhood-esque innocence as if she’s still young which contradicts the first lyric

So what does it mean? Right now, she and Tyler are blissfully stuck in the period of early adulthood where responsibilities start to appear but don’t dominate their lives (hence having the time to “hit the 405”).
Hypnotized by the lights

Reference to the song “Hypnotized” by Purple Disco Machine and shows she is somewhat hypnotized.

In that song we hear the lyrics:
“I’m coming home, I’m coming back down tonight
‘Cause I’ve been hypnotized by Hypnotized by the lights meaning the lights of Los Angeles/the strip as she refers to in the verse before talking about 405(meaning the interstate 405..Los Angeles….) she’s hypnotized by the lights of LA…also maybe hypnotized by the blinding lights of LA fame…
Maybe we can hit the 405

This could either be referring to
1.  Interstate 405, which runs through southern California and Los Angeles. or
2. The area code for central Oklahoma.

body.plain: “Time Machine” is the third track from Willow’s third album WILLOW. The song is about being born in the wrong generation – something Willow always talks about feeling like – and wanting to go back in time.

annotations: I’d go back to 1993
This is ten years later after 1983, which enables Willow to rhyme. It could also be a reference to how music was appreciated and structured that year.
Maybe I would play with Kurt Cobain
Kurt Cobain was an american singer-songwriter who was also the lead singer in the band Nirvana.
Maybe I would get on MTV
During the 90s, MTV dominated the music advertising, helping to boost the careers of many artists and becoming the go-to channel for the best new music.
Maybe I would chill with Basquiat

Jean-Michel Basquiat was a famous artist in the 80s best known for his Neo-Expressionist art.



 Basquiat in 1985 with an untitled painting
I’d go back to 1983

On January 1, 1983, research network ARPANET officially adopted the process that would go on to make the idea of Internet a reality.

By wanting to back to this specific year when the Internet was in its early stages, Willow believes that she would be happier in the time when an all-consuming Internet hadn’t created a new foundational place filled with hatred, judgement and people idolizing and aspiring towards false, empty lifestyles.

Everyone is disconnected these days
 ’Cause everyone is looking at their phone
 Tryna feel like they are less alone (So wrong)
 And I’m here to tell them that they’re wrong (So wrong)

The 21st century is a highly technologic dependent time period for society. People have gotten more personally disconnected with each other ever since smartphones were developed, and Willow is aware of this.  Social media has proven to lower self esteem and make users depressed based off posting content they themselves believe is their reality. For example, a lot of people may post on instagram a lavish life, but behind the camera, everything can be fake.

And tell me does it feel like that?
 Does it really feel like that?
 ’Cause baby, if it’s real like that...

These lines show Willow desperately wanting to know what life was in the 80s was like then. Perception is truly reality; if she had the chance to time travel back, it’s unlikely that she would return to her original time, which she further expresses in the chorus.
21st Century me, 20th Century dreams
Being how Willow is from the 21st century, she would time travel back to the 20th to live the life she always wanted. This phrase adds an oxymoronic longing for the latter time period.

Since they seem to have trust issues, which where established in Willows second bar, this sadness might be why they connect.

Since emo culture had a huge influence on modern rap (e.g. Juice Wrld, Lil Peep, etc.) the modern emo girl now listens to hip-hop instead of punk and rock.

She is introverted and cannot open herself up to others. She does not trust Willow and so does she.

She might look cute on the outside, but there is more to her and if she gets mad she can make you feel tortured agony.

Thigh-high fishnets and some black boots
 Nose pierced with the cigarette perfume

Fashion is an important part of youth culture, especially of the emo subculture.
With this line MGK is describing what one would imagine an emo girl looking like.
This line may be inspired by american underground emo/pop-punk band “August is Falling” who also frequently mention the emo dresscode like in their eponymous single: “I’m staring at your letters, through the holes in your sweater”.

https://youtu.be/w-9fyRnczzo

I fell in love with an emo girl
 I’m in love with an emo girl
 I fell in love with an emo girl
 All I want is an emo girl

He fell in love with an emo girl.

Really had to look this one up you big dummy?
She’s got makeup by the mirror in her bedroom

While this imagery is fairly average for a woman who wears makeup, MGK shared on The Late Late Show in February 2022 that his verse is inspired by Jennifer Check from 2009 film Jennifer’s Body. In the movie, Jennifer’s room is filled with mirrors and makeup.
Kiss me, holy fuck, I’m bleeding on your Blink tee

Blink-182 is an American rock band formed in Poway, California, in 1992. Their current lineup consists of guitarist/vocalist Tom DeLonge, bassist/vocalist Mark Hoppus, and drummer Travis Barker.

Travis Barker happens to also be the drummer for this song and many of MGK’s songs.

The music video helps explain this line further. She’s referring to a kind of choker necklace that has spikes on it. When she leans in to kiss someone wearing this necklace, it pokes her and causes her to bleed on the person’s Blink-182 shirt.

It is also possible that she is bleeding due to her cutting herself, which is reinforced by the line at the end of the verse ‘You tell me you’re depressed, baby girl, that makes two of us.’ People who are depressed often cut themselves as a coping mechanism to relieve stress and distract themselves from their problems.

annotations:
I want to, want to, want to touch you
 Want to touch you, but my fingertips are numb
 I want to, want to, want to love you
 Want to love you, but my chest is tightenin’ up
 I want to, want to, want to feel like I can chill
Fingertips are numb, chest is tightening up, and the desire to chill but they can’t are all possible symptoms of anxiety and/or a panic attack.

Wow, moment’s gone now
 Know you wanna stay, but I think I gotta leave right now

Camila suggests she spent so much time obsessing over her past and what others say about her online, she ruined what could have been quality time spent with her loved ones, thus distancing herself from friends and love interests. This leaves her with the impression that she is a “psychofreak” for overthinking to the point where it alienates other people.
House in the hills is a house of cards
“The Hills” is a reference to Beverly Hills. A house in this area could be a fragile one or an unpredictable one due to the stigmas of competitive superficiality that it holds.
House in the hills is a house of cards

A few months ago, Camila sold the home she shared in Hollywood Hills due to a break-in. During the COVID-19 pandemic, she and her ex-partner Shawn Mendes lived there together and as a lot of Familia is rumored to be about him, her former home and memories with Shawn is most likely what this line is referring to. A ‘house of cards’ is defined as a shaky structure or foundation, so Camila might be describing her and Shawn’s relationship with this phrase.
On the other hand, a house on a hill, however pompous it may be, is more likely to suffer from the weather due to the lack of natural elements that protect it. It may refer to her being exposed to the media and the opinion of other people, she is more likely to fall apart. She might not be referencing her relationship with Shawn simply because the song was written since June and the house was sold in December.
In the bathroom while my friends laugh on the couch

Camila has talked before, in the lead-up to her debut album, about recording songs in the hotel bathroom while she was still a member of Fifth Harmony. There was also a night where the official Fifth Harmony account posted a picture of 4 out of 5 of the members in the recording studio (minus Camila) and Camila asserted that she was also there that night. Given the previous lines about Fifth Harmony, this line is potentially about Camila recording songs in the bathroom while the rest of the band were having fun together.
Give me lemonade, I give you limes

“When life gives you lemons, make lemonade” is a common quote that means to take the opportunities life gives you, and find positivity in dark times. However in this lyric, Camila says “Give me lemonade, I give you limes”, twisting up the original quote a little and implying that when something good happened in her life, it all turned sour.
Blink and the fairytale falls apart

Camila made her acting debut in the 2021 remake of the popular fairytale Cinderella, starring as Cinderella herself. Camila revealed her tendency to daydream and fantasise about her life in her interview with Genius: Verified.
She explores the idea of her partner not following the script of the fairytale she has created her in mind in the first verse of “Don’t Go Yet”

I replayed this moment for months
Alone in my head, waitin' for it to come
I wrote all your lines in the script in my mind
And I’d hoped that you’d follow it for once
On my Instagram talkin’ ’bout “I’m healed”

Camila often takes to her Instagram account to share her journey of mindfulness, meditation and gratitude.

In this line, “she satirises her own reliance on recovery clichés” – Nick Levine, NME.

Everybody says they miss the old me
 I been on this ride since I was fifteen
 I don’t blame the girls for how it went down, down

Camila Cabello auditioned for The X Factor in 2012 at the age of 15. After initially being eliminated, she was brought back to form the girl group Fifth Harmony along with Lauren Jauregui, Dinah Jane, Normani and Ally Brooke.

On December 18, 2016, it was announced via a post on the group’s Twitter account that Camila was leaving Fifth Harmony, who later made a statement on her Twitter account:



In this lyric, Camila implies that she doesn’t know which “old her” people are talking about and doesn’t even know how to get there anymore, as she is now 25 years old—a decade of growth and change has occurred. She also acknowledges that she doesn’t blame her former bandmates for what went down, and suggests that she has moved on from the past.

Additionally, the repetition of the word “down” could be a reference to Fifth Harmony’s “Down,” the band’s first single following her departure.

annotations:
Not negative, just different
 You wanna have lunch, and I wanna have a picnic
 You wanna go up, I wanna just fly all night

Here, willow explains how she feels different. She is in a different reality, her own, where she seems free and dreamy (the term picnic is a subcategory of the term lunch, everyone have lunch but only some have picnic). She doesn’t want to go up like everyone else, she just want to let herself be carried by life.

If only I could stay, if only I could pray
 If only I could wait, if only you could stay
 Up, up in your zone, yes, you’re all alone
 Yes I’m all alone

Willow refers to the moment in which her consciousness and herself are connected and she is not aware of time or space, in which she feels safe and herself, but the way life is, it is hard or impossible to stay in that place forever.

In that moment she is alone with her consciousness who are one.

It’s three, it’s three, it’s me, it’s Moi, it’s Jay, it’s all these days
 My days are numbered, you can come through

Willow is mentioning maybe the most 3 important people in her life. Not to mention, the title of this project is 3.

“Moi” Moisés Arias, is known for his role as Rico on the Disney show Hannah Montana, is a good friend of willow and her brother. Also known for being in the controversial picture where he is shown in the same bed as Willow.

“Jay” is of course referring to her brother Jaden Smith.

Willow has been enlightened with the heavy knowledge that we are not alone. She is extremely intelligent and beyond talented for her age. She believes that our days are numbered due to the actions of certain humans on this planet, and also that no one can physically live forever.

Getting in the car, we cruisin’
 Going down the PCH, I’m going to get a smoothie

PCH means Pacific Coast Highway.

Also a reference to her brother Jaden Smith’s 2014 song “PCH” that features Willow.
